threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary, masquerading as 'ChromeUpdate', is an infostealer. It displays a fake system dialog box prompting the user for their password with the message 'The application `ChromeUpdate` wants to make changes.'. It then exfiltrates the stolen password, along with the system's external IP address (retrieved from `api.ipify.org`), to a hardcoded Dropbox account using the Dropbox API (`content.dropboxapi.com/2/files/upload`). The malware uses hardcoded API keys and tokens to authenticate with Dropbox.
